cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI

The paper uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model trained on satellite imagery to extract landscape features, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper incorporates these features into an infectious disease prediction model, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical modeling (cs.LG). The use of satellite imagery also suggests that the paper may fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
